==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trysail
<hw>Try"sail</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
fore-and-aft sail, bent to a gaff, and hoisted on a lower mast or on a
small mast, called the <xex>trysail mast</xex>, close abaft a lower
mast; -- used chiefly as a storm sail. Called also
<altname>spencer</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Try-square</ent>⟦br⟧
